values: and it so turns out that on Friday night there was this party, the one that I told u about that we didn't get invited to. well, one of the American kids was drunk and had random sex with a German kid in front of people. that appalls me. just wanted to tell u all. and on Monday, tomorrow, we go to a concentration camp in Frankreich. yippee!

OK, so I know I know I am behind a little...perhaps a few days, but I have been kinda busy doing this and that and it just seems to have consumed my well being. First of all, the plane ride out of BWI took 6 hours and I sat next to two wonderful girls. One was from Severna Park and the other was half Swedish half American who had been living in Ireland for the past 6 years. We all just sat there in out seats the whole time talking and it felt good to socialize instead of drift off in my own little world.

We landed in Iceland at about 6am Icelandic time. UK is 1 hour ahead, Germany 2, East Coast 4. We got onto a bus cuz we were to take a tour of Iceland in a tour bus. We saw the volcanic landscape and stopped to see the plates where N. America and Europe are splitting, we saw the boiling geysers. We went to the cliffs and the view was just breathtaking. I took a lot of pictures so don't any of you worry, ya'll be well endowed sooner or later. Next we went to the Blue Lagoon. It is this huge hot spring crated by the geysers and the water is this beautiful blue. It is said that this water has minerals that help with ailments, but I have yet to see the affects of their minerals. I bought a post card so that  I can look back and be like, "Hey, I was there!" We got back onto to the plane after that and spent 2 hours on route to Frankfurt.
Tomorrow is the day! I am sorrowfully excited.
